<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 09 at 12:40AM CST  by NWS Houston - Galveston</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of eastern Trinity and
central Polk Counties through 115 AM CST...
At 1239 AM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Seven Oaks, or 8 miles north of Livingston, moving northeast at 25
mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Corrigan, Seven Oaks, Leggett and Moscow.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
